{# Joint-organisers strip (Issue #198).

   Renders a horizontal row of co-organising institutions for joint
   events, so the collaboration footprint reads as a structured
   component rather than buried in body prose.

   Required argument:
     jointOrgs — array of { name, url?, logo? } objects.
                   name  required, plain text
                   url   optional, omit to render the name as plain
                         text instead of a link
                   logo  optional, path under /assets/images/. When
                         set, renders the logo next to the name.
                         When unset, the name carries on its own.

   Optional argument:
     jointOrgsLabel — short heading shown to the left of the list.
                      Defaults to "Jointly organised with" but can
                      be overridden, e.g. "Hosts", "In partnership
                      with", or the locale equivalent.

   Example call from a conference page:

     {%- set jointOrgs = [
       { name: "Stockholm University", url: "https://www.su.se/",
         logo: "/assets/images/partners/stockholm-uni.svg" },
       { name: "NetSec (COST Action CA24154)",
         url: "https://netsec-cost.eu/" }
     ] -%}
     {% include "joint-orgs.njk" %}

   No-op when `jointOrgs` is empty or undefined, so it's safe to
   include conditionally without guarding at each call site. -#}
{%- if jointOrgs and (jointOrgs | length) > 0 -%}
<div class="joint-orgs" role="complementary" aria-label="{{ jointOrgsLabel or 'Jointly organised with' }}">
  <span class="joint-orgs-label">{{ jointOrgsLabel or 'Jointly organised with' }}</span>
  <ul class="joint-orgs-list">
    {%- for org in jointOrgs %}
    <li>
      {%- if org.logo %}
      <img class="joint-orgs-logo"
           src="{{ org.logo }}"
           alt="{{ org.name }}"
           loading="lazy">
      {%- endif %}
      {%- if org.url %}
      <a href="{{ org.url }}" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="joint-orgs-name">{{ org.name }}</a>
      {%- else %}
      <span class="joint-orgs-name">{{ org.name }}</span>
      {%- endif %}
    </li>
    {%- endfor %}
  </ul>
</div>
{%- endif -%}
